description:
Description

You are given an integer ‘n’, determine if it can be expressed as a product of binary numbers. For example: 55 cannot be represented as product of binary numbers but 1210 can be represented as product of binary numbers (1210 = 11* 11 *10).

If it can be represented print “YES” else print “NO”.


Sample Input:

n= 14641


Sample output:

YES

Explanation:

Since, 14641 can be represented as 11* 11* 11*11 which are all binary numbers (containing only 0 or 1 as their digit) thus the answer is YES.


Constraints:

1<=n<=10^5
title: Is Binary?
